text.tspan: Notes: YIELD or STOP signs are used only at passive crossings.
A STOP sign is used only if an engineering study
determines that it is appropriate for that particular
Mounting height shall be at least 7 feet for sidewalks where the lateral
offset is less than 2 feet, at least 4 feet for sidewalks where the lateral
offset is 2 feet or more, and at least 4 feet for pathways.
Measured to the elevation at the near edge of the pathway or sidewalk.
